Text.Value: Did you think I wouldn't find out?
No...
You realised the error of your ways, and corrected them.
I do trust you. I just like to have insurance.
I regretted it the moment I signed it.
Be that as it may, Orpheus deserves to be free.
I promise I won't use the hammer.
I hope your ambitions end there.
Act upon your disbelief, and you will not even live to regret your actions.
No.
Risked mind, limb, and freedom.
I'm disappointed to hear that.
No.
And even if you survived him, what of the elder brain? Without the protection I leverage for you, you would be enthralled in an instant.
I trust you saw the error of your ways. Do not err again.
All to steal the Orphic Hammer.
You saw for yourself what the Chosen are capable of.
I destroyed it. You should be happy.
Good. If we can count upon each other, then we may count one advantage in our favour.
Still, you would test our alliance.
But you have merely ironed out a wrinkle.
You're a mind flayer. Can you blame me for not trusting you?
But did you also see their weakness?
I'll find another way to survive. One that doesn't involve abusing a githyanki.
I have already told you that the githyanki prince only wants to see you dead. But it seems you still do not trust me.
Yes, in a manner of speaking.
There is only one thing to understand about a devil - it serves only itself. Anything it promised to deliver, it would recover tenfold.
The contract you tried to hide from me.
I never asked to be stuck with you.
Did you think that you would quietly infiltrate the devil's home with me nestled right within your thoughts, and mask your true intentions from me?
His domination is what keeps you free. You know this already.
You slaughtered a devil in his own home, and returned empty-handed? You've made better decisions.

EditorData.NodeContext: All Emperor lines in this scene, telepathic.

Text.Value: That's what I thought.
Let me into the Prism. I trust Gith's heir over a wretched ghaik.
Ego?
You are falling into the same trap as the Chosen.
But you would do better not to err in the first place. Especially when there is so much at stake.
Yes. Precisely.
Not even a little bit.
I'll never trust you, for as long as you keep Orpheus chained.
I'll work with you, but I'll never trust you.
I was curious. I wanted to understand what the devil had to offer.
Orpheus should not be dominated.
All right. You've made your point.
I... don't know.
They had an almost flawless plan to dominate Faern. But their distrust is their undoing.
Their distrust of one another is their undoing.
Us?
Open the Prism. I trust Gith's heir over a wretched ghaik.
That is not my definition of trust.
We must not make the same mistake. We must work together.
A curious thing - to enter into a devil's home, and make it out alive.

EditorData.NodeContext: All Emperor lines in this scene, telepathic.

Text.Value: Good. Then you did the right thing by destroying it.
Careful. You will make a mind flayer laugh.
Fine. From now on, I trust you.
Nonetheless, our fates are bound. And in the absence of a happier union, I will accept a useful one.
The contract you never should have signed.
Each other?
I could say the same of you.
I wish I could trust you, but that you felt you needed to have it at all tells me that you are not worthy of that trust.
So you wormed your way into the devil's lair.

EditorData.NodeContext: All Emperor lines in this scene, telepathic.

Text.Value: And what then?
It was their union that made them.
And destroyed the contract that bound you.
You may think yourself ingenious for having slain a devil.
After all we shared...
The elder brain will not be such an easy foe.
So you keep saying, but why should I believe you?
When he wakens from his incarceration, what do you think he will make of you? The one who bears the spawn his very nature bends him to revile?
We must not fall into the same trap. We must trust one another.
It is time we resume our journey to find it.

Synopsis:
Emperor talks to player after they leave House of Hope.

All Emperor lines are telepathic.
